pulses.name: 20241016 Most Active Threat Indicators
pulses.description:
16 Oct 2024 : Most Active Threat Indicators
#Cybersecurity #Cyberattack #RCE #Botnet #IOC

Top 3 Source Countries:

- China (CN): The most active source of cyber attacks, particularly through the Mozi botnet and various command execution vulnerabilities, indicating a strong presence in exploiting network devices.
- India (IN): Notable for its involvement in multiple attacks, especially targeting routers with command injection vulnerabilities and the Mozi botnet, reflecting a diverse range of cyber threats from this region.
- United States (US): Involved in various attacks, including the use of Nmap scanners and the SystemBC botnet, highlighting its role in both offensive and defensive cybersecurity activities.

pulses.name: Threat Intel Report - W34-2024
pulses.description:
This is a cyber-advisory document, presenting the compiled cyber threat intelligence sourced from various channels and tools. 

These are weekly base recommendations to all IT Administrators and CISOs to take corrective actions to upgrade their security infrastructure against newly identified threats and attacks in this week. 

Security is a continuous process, and it has to be reviewed and audited on a continuous manner through manual or automated tools. 

These details may be used as an additional layer to verify the current security posture of an organization against latest cyber trends.
